// TEST: Physics -- Free Deconvolution: Cleaning the Observer's Estimated Spectrum
// ============================================================================
// Example 30 established the law: an observer estimating a d-register tower
// from N samples has FREE spectral noise with deformation gamma = d/N. This
// example puts the law to WORK -- the arc's noise-robustness gap, opened
// with the correct error model. An internal observer estimates the
// covariance tower of a real fuzzy system and recovers the TRUE spectral
// moments from the biased estimate by free deconvolution: subtract the
// noise at the free-cumulant level, where (and only where) it is additive.
// The system: the 96 bond-transmission registers rt_j = 2 m_j/(m_j+m_(j+1))
// of a 97-ball fuzzy chain, every mass an iid 3-point jet {0.92, 1.0, 1.08}.
// Bond-locality makes the true covariance EXACTLY tridiagonal Toeplitz
// (only neighboring bonds share a mass), so the truth is fully analytic and
// computed in-language: entries (e0, v0, v1) as exact 9- and 27-term digit
// sums, spectrum lambda_k = v0 + 2 v1 cos(pi k/97) (path-graph bands --
// after the half-line (25), S_n (22), and circle (28), the SPECTRUM itself
// now carries the tower). The observer sees N = 192 chain realizations
// (emitted digit table, data-only, audited in-file); gamma = 96/192 = 1/2.
// FINDINGS (pinned):
//   * THE RAW SPECTRUM IS BADLY BIASED: m2 of the estimated covariance
//     comes out 33.5% above truth (rres2/tm2), m3 +103%, m4 +129% -- at
//     half-budget the observer's spectral tower is mostly noise shape.
//   * FREE DECONVOLUTION RECOVERS THE TRUTH: inverting the free forward
//     model (a triangular system in the moments, gamma known) lands within
//     0.45% / 2.7% / 5.8% of the exact spectral moments -- improvement
//     factors 74x / 38x / 40x over the raw estimate at k = 2 / 3 / 4.
//   * THE CLASSICAL NOISE MODEL FAILS STRUCTURALLY: treating spectral
//     noise as an independent additive perturbation (same noise moments,
//     classical convolution) leaves residuals 12.5x / 15.5x the free
//     residuals at k = 3 / 4. The terms it cannot see -- 3 gamma m1 m2 and
//     gamma(4 m1 m3 + 2 m2^2), the SIGNAL-NOISE COUPLING -- are exactly
//     where free and classical convolution differ: eigenvalue noise is not
//     additive on eigenvalues; it is additive on free cumulants.
//   * THE FORWARD MODEL IS CONFIRMED IN THE DATA: free-convolving the
//     analytic truth forward predicts the observer's raw moments to
//     0.05% / 1.2% / 2.5% -- both directions of the dictionary work.
//   * Fine print worth keeping: v1/v0 = -0.4999997 -- the transfer kernel
//     is log-additive to O(w^4) (f = (ln m_j - ln m_(j+1))/2 + ...), and
//     any additive antisymmetric bond kernel gives exactly -1/2; tm1 = v0
//     exactly (the cosine band is mean-centered over path modes). A first
//     attempt used the 6-mass cascade's 24 lag-family registers: their
//     truth is a ~6-spike spectrum (24 observables of 6 latents), and
//     there the error is spike-position FLUCTUATION, not MP bias -- moment
//     deconvolution barely helped (improvement ~1.4x at d = 24). Flat-bulk
//     truths are where moment-level cleaning shines; spiked truths need
//     eigenvector-resolved estimators (Ledoit-Peche) -- the honest boundary
//     of this method, and the next rung.
// Consequence for the arc: every "is this tower degenerate/realizable"
// verdict downstream of an ESTIMATED spectrum -- invariant detection,
// Hankel rank, generator spectra -- should run on the free-deconvolved
// moments, not the raw ones, whenever registers are many and looks are
// few. The observer's uncertainty calculus is free (ex 30); this example
// is that calculus, used.
// Data provenance: 192 x 97 iid digit table from a minstd LCG (seed
// 424242), emitted by a data-only generator; in-file audits: digit mean
// 0.9944 (pinned), e0 = 1 exactly (jet symmetry), truth side entirely
// closed-form in-language.
// ============================================================================
let DIG: Array<Int64 like Idx<192>, Idx<97>> = [
